                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="5" precision="low"/></name> <supplied reason="lost" cert="high"><g type="punct">⋮</g></supplied> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65359"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Πολύαρχος">Πολυάρχ<unclear>ω</unclear></name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλλ</supplied><unclear>ω</unclear>νι</name></persName> 
                    <g type="punct">⋮</g> <w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάτ<supplied reason="lost">αν</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ος"><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="5" precision="medium"/><seg part="F">ον</seg></name> <g type="punct">⋮</g> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-66133"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Χαῖνυς">Χαίνυος</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="3a"/><space quantity="4" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="5" precision="low"/> <supplied reason="lost" cert="high"><g type="punct">⋮</g></supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="3">
                        <lem><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="5" precision="medium"/>ον</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>ον</rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Untel</supplied> fils de Polyarkhos <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré</supplied> à Apollon au titre de la dîme 
            <supplied reason="subaudible">la statue de</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os fils de Khainus.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">So-and-so</supplied> son of Polyarchos <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated</supplied> to Apollo as a tithe 
            <supplied reason="subaudible">the statue of</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os son of Chainys.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Il tale</supplied> figlio di Polyarchos <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato</supplied> ad Apollo come decima 
            <supplied reason="subaudible">la statua di</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os figlio di Chainys.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This inscription was published by Pugliese Carratelli from a photograph in the Antiquities Archives, which mentioned the findspot as given above. He was not able to trace the stone.</p>
                <p>In the vacat under line 3, some letters were scratched later on, especially an omicron (or a meaningless circle?) which is much visible on the photograph.</p>
	<p>For another occurrence of a son of Chainys, see at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr099100</ref>, which however does not allow a secure restoration here.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
